result.execSummary:
The defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Danielle L. Shelton in court, defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel withdrew her bail motion and requested a plea and sentencing date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 21, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Danielle L. Shelton in court, defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel in a lengthy motion hearing in Branch 17.  Case continued to 3/02/15 at 1:30 p.m. for bail hearing and scheduling conference.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Defense Counsel requests sequestration of all State's witnesses.  Sworn for the state:Gregory Borst-MPD Officer.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and pleads not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 20.  Scheduling conference scheduled for February 26, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Notice of Motion and Motion for Review and Modification of Bail filed by Atty. Danielle L. Shelton.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with SEBASTIAN H. DAMIAN W. AND ROSHON S.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION INCLUDING DRUG TESTING.
   Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription AND dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Defendant Giovannis G Rodriguez in custody.  Nathaniel E Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge MORONEY, Branch 20.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
